data.description:
1. SEC accepts Grayscale XRP Trust Conversion ETF application and starts the review process;
2. SEC has received DOGE ETF applications submitted by Grayscale and NYSE;
3. Coinbase financial report: Full-year revenue in 2024 reached $6.6 billion, net profit reached $2.6 billion;
4. The US court agreed to suspend the legal dispute between Binance and the SEC until April, and both parties must submit reports before April 14;
5. Trump's World Liberty Finance purchased millions of dollars of MOVE and WBTC in the past 3 hours;
6. Jupiter: 50% of the agreement fee will be used to repurchase JUP and locked for 3 years;
7. GameStop is considering investing in Bitcoin and other cryptocurrencies;
8. BTC options worth $2.08 billion will expire today, with the biggest pain point of $98,000;
9. Bloomberg ETF analyst: Litecoin ETF may become the earliest approved new crypto ETF;
10. Fireblocks executives: X Money is expected to support crypto payments by the end of the year.
